All the positive samples from 43 pig farms were amplified and sequenced based on specific primers designed by our lab as described previously (Table 1
) (Zhou et al., 2012). And 15 PEDV representative strains were selected from 43 acquired sequences of all the positive PEDV samples. Then a phylogenetic tree was constructed by the neighbor-joining method (NJ) using MEGA 7.0 based on these representative strains and another 60 representative PEDV strains with complete S gene sequences available in GenBank. Also, the complete amino acid sequence of these strains were aligned using Clustal W method of MegAlign (DNAStar Lasergene) (Table 2
).
